headline: CNN Live Event/Special
subHeadline: CNN New Year's Eve Live. Aired 12-1a ET

utterances.speaker: ANDERSON COOPER, CNN ANCHOR
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year! Twenty -- it is already 2025, that's crazy!

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We should do a toast. We should do a toast.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, so can we do a toast?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I mean, we did one off camera. But it doesn't count if it's off camera.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- if it doesn't happen on camera. It doesn't happen.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I have to say that was really beautiful.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And I kept my phone down the whole time and experienced it. And basically, what happens is, they do the countdown. And then they flip it right into New York, New York which --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: All right, I mean as if this is necessary.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Cheers. Hey, everybody, thanks for hanging out with us.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Thanks for all the love. And I hope 2025 is everything you wanted it to be --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I really hope we don't get fired.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well, sweetie I think -- I don't think you're going to get fired.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Amazing stuff coming up. All right.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Like we haven't plugged you in yet.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Whatever. I mean, the mayor's still running around.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Be kind because everybody you meet is fighting a great battle.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes. I know the battle he's fighting, because every (INAUDIBLE) a bunch of indictments. That's what he's fighting.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Dial it down, bring it into the new year right. All right.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: We don't want to wake up in the morning with I should (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm going to wake up with (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Because my son is going to wake us -- wake me up --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: My son's going to wake up (INAUDIBLE). You know what, I'm going to do? I'm going to go home. And I'm going to go into my son -- to Wyatt's room and I'm going to go to sleep in Wyatt's room tonight.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Well guess what? Before that we're going to go crash Patti LuPone's New Year's Eve party.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Cheers. Oh gosh. This will be -- I just want to say this is the last drink I'm going to have of 2025.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I mean (INAUDIBLE) even get this outfit.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I mean Richard you have committed -- the truth is. I mean, I got to give you a microphone. There's a lot going on here.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Bring your husband here. I think (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: This is the husband? You're gay?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm scared to stand next to you.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Is the pain of -- of the gay experience.

utterances.speaker: QUEST
utterances.sentences: I know, but look at this. I know (INAUDIBLE). What a great night. You guys were amazing.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It was a great night. It was a great night.(CROSSTALK)

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How long did it take you and where do you see?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Not that long? Well, his dress (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: QUEST
utterances.sentences: Wait, I just sort of wander around.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How long have you been at CNN?

utterances.speaker: QUEST
utterances.sentences: Because I was doing Times Square for another place. It's about my 30th year in Times Square.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: By the way, I just want to -- I just want to point out I just want to say Aaron Brown died yesterday, I don't know it's (INAUDIBLE). And he made a huge mark at CNN.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I work with him at ABC.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And I just I admired him so much and I just want to give a shout-out.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: No, I'm glad you did. And he used to have me on many --(CROSSTALK)

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, by the way, his producer David Borman (ph) who produced World News Now at ABC and created the show with Aaron was a show that saved me at ABC.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Coming up next, two special guests join us on the riser.Plus, as we go to break, a surprise performance --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- to the New Year's celebration here in Times Square.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Joining us now are our two lookalikes that we met earlier.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And here is the Anderson lookalike.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yes, I know. First of all --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And where are you originally from?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: OK. Now by the way, I had no -- I did not attend any production meetings. So, I didn't know that Andy was arranging this. Andy picked Stanley (ph) --

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: And, you as my doppelganger, which I got to say, if I could look like you, I would be --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: This more importantly, this is my doppelganger right here. And we sprayed your hair gray -- UNIDENTIFIED MALE

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: By the way, Stanley (ph) is Andy's trainer.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. And what I want to say, and we all celebrated --

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK, hold on. What I want to say -- OK. What I want to say is, as we all celebrated New Year's together on the platform, I was looking at you, Stanley (ph), and Stanley (ph) has been my trainer for some time, and he's from the Ukraine.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And he moved here 14 years ago.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And he did not speak a lick of English.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And he was a house painter. And he worked at McDonald's.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And he came here pursuing the American dream. And he did not -- he learned English. He became a U.S. citizen.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: He built an incredible training business.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And here you are, you're a U.S. citizen.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: And tell me what it felt like to be in Times Square, where I know you've never been, on New Year's Eve. What did that feel like?

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.sentences: It feels incredible. Amazing, powerful, strong, beautiful. I love it.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm so proud of you for everything you've become.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Honestly, you are -- you are the embodiment -- embodiment of the American dream.(CROSSTALK)

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: He is the embodiment of the American dream. He is. Sorry. OK. All right. OK. We (INAUDIBLE).

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I have no story like that.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK, very good. All right. OK. Thank you, lookalikes. You can move on.Anderson, let's wrap out the show.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We want to thank you for being with us tonight.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Anything else? I mean we have.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We had like nine shots tonight.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: The hurricane happened. Everybody said to me, you have to show this guy a knife.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I'm not even anything. This one, I don't know.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK, are we going to crash Patti LuPone's party? Maybe. We'll see. OK.You all, thank you for having me on CNN. That does it for us and our lookalikes. Do you want to do this or should I do this? Let me do this. Happy New Year everyone. Sarah, Carrie and Harry are going to continue our coverage next from Austin, Texas. We are going to leave you with Meghan Trainor performing one of her hit songs at the iconic Red Rocks Amphitheater.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Thank you so much for joining us on this night. And we wish you a very happy new year in 2025.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We got to get out of here.

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED FEMALE
utterances.sentences: Akwaaba, Andy, and Anderson. That means hello in Fante, which is the native language of Ghana. It's appropriate because I'm standing right here in the capital, Accra, to celebrate New Year's Eve.This is a historic night. This is the first time that Ghana's New Year's Eve celebration is done globally. OK, so the clock is winding down to 2025. So, everyone is going to help me. Ten, nine, eight, seven, six, five, four, three, two, one. UNIDENTIFIED SPEAKERS (in unison): Ten, nine, eight, seven, six, five, four, three, two, one. (FOREIGN LANGUAGE) (COMMERCIAL BREAK)

utterances.speaker: UNIDENTIFIED MALE
utterances.sentences: That's right, Emmy for life (ph), and we can't wait to see 2025, more great performances in our house. What up, Rick?

utterances.speaker: RICKY BELL, MEMBER OF NEW EDITION
utterances.sentences: And we'd like to wish everyone watching a very happy New Year!

utterances.speaker: ANNOUNCER
utterances.sentences: Welcome to CNN's New Year's Eve Live with performances and appearances by 50 Cent, New Edition, Sting, Shania Twain, Adam DeVine, and Third Eye Blind. And now your hosts, live from Austin, Texas, Sara Sidner, Cari Champion, and Harry Enten.CARI CHAMPION, JOURNALIST/TELEVISION PERSONALITY: We are live! Yay!

utterances.speaker: HARRY ENTEN, CNN POLITICS SENIOR WRITER AND ANALYST
SIDNER
utterances.sentences: What you're hearing behind us, by the way, is Third Eye Blind. They are rocking it out. The party obviously continuing here in Austin, Texas.And we are here to make sure that we help keep the city slogan going, which is "Keep Austin weird."

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: And I think that we three are able --

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK, OK, but you're not weird.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I'm the only weird one without a hat. What? But Harry's hat -- Harry's hat, is he suggesting the Buffalo Bills are winning the Super Bowl?

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: We are absolutely going the entire way, baby. We're finally going to do it. Four Super Bowl losses. We're finally going to get a Super Bowl win behind MVP Josh Allen. You heard it here first.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: What's the data on that, sir? What's the data? Talk to Sara and I.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: Look, there are some times for data. Those are for election nights. But for New Year's Eve, we're throwing the data out the window.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: And I'm telling you this. The Buffalo Bills are going all the way. Because where would you rather be than right here, right now?

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK, so we'll roll the tape back on Super Bowl --

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Right. When the Rams win the Super Bowl.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: The Bills and Rams can both be in the Super Bowl.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK, OK. I'm in agreement. I'm in agreement with Sara right now. OK. So --

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: I would like to thank Harry.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: We're keeping it weird; we promise. We've got so much going on here today.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: We've brought you a whole entire gospel band made up of family members.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: So, five sisters, four brothers and papa, who's also the bishop. They are here. The Jones Family Singers.We've got some dancing that we are going to take part in.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK. So, it's a little bit of --

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: It's a Jewish New Yorker dance. OK? I'm like Elaine Benes, all right.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: You should try out for the U.T. dancers. I mean, they --

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: We're going to -- You're going to see my try-out a little bit later on.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: It's all in the hip. But Harry's got it down. He's got it down.But we've got a lot of things. Oh!

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Take me back to my childhood.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Do you want to start together?

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Yes.CHAMPION (singing): Can you stand the rain? SIDNER (singing): Can you stand the rain?

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: I'm going to let you two do that. Thank you.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: -- Biv DeVoe. OK. They're still a part of New Year's.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Ronnie, Bobby, Ricky and Mike, I love you.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I love a girl. Who cares who you like? OK.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: Yes, we've got Sting. We've got -- We've got Sting. We've got New Edition and Sting. And, you know, he's my favorite member of the Police, so I'm very much looking forward to that.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: He is the ultimate performer. His music is, like, iconic. You can't -- you can't not like Sting.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: He's got so many songs. Plus, the Police. I was -- I'm a big fan.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: I think I look like him a little bit.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Sara, you have such an eclectic taste in music.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You love -- You love pop. You love hip hop. You love it all.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: So, we're going to -- we're going to defer to her for all music tonight.But I do want to point out to everyone who is here watching you came a day early to do what?

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: So, Harry was coming, a boy from the Bronx. And I was, like, you need to see what country is like. So, we went out about an hour outside of Austin to the Natural Bridge Wildlife Ranch.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: There we are in the car. And I said, Harry, you've got to do this with me.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: Well, what I want to point out, though, is you took us on this adventure, and the place supposedly closes at 4 p.m. We did not learn that it closed until four, until we were ten minutes out. We looked at the clock, and it was 3

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: Sara says, I'm going to try it. She goes around the closed gate, says, "What time is it open tomorrow?"And they say, "Nine a.m." And the guy waits two beats and then goes, "You guys want to come in right now?"

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I got to point out something really quickly --

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: -- so folks at home can see. This is a longhorn. But I said, Sara. What? What is that that we're looking at? And you said --

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: I said, that's a ram. And there was a buffalo. So, I said the rams versus the buffalo.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: OK, so there was a battle?

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: It's a sign. That is the Super Bowl. The Bills versus the Rams.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I might -- I might have to disagree.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: You know what? Disagree. We'll see where we are in a month. CHAMPION

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: All right. I'll tell you what we do know.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: My girl is in the Bahamas at Atlantis Paradise island. She's partying like a royal.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: She does get the best gigs. And she looks hot sauce. Stephanie Elam is there with singer Ellie Gould -- Goulding. And. Oh! Oh, look at that hair and that outfit.

utterances.speaker: STEPHANIE ELAM, CNN CORRESPONDENT
utterances.sentences: You know what? I -- I'm trying to be beautiful like you guys. And I'm also -- happy New Year to you, because we are living in the future. So happy New Year from 2025.And I want you to know that Ellie Goulding just got off stage and brought everyone into 2025, and she killed it. She was out there singing and jumping and athletic. How do you do that? How do you hit those notes? How do you do that and stay so active while you're on stage the whole time?

utterances.speaker: ELLIE GOULDING, SINGER
utterances.sentences: Honestly, I do a lot of running on the treadmill and singing at the same time.

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: I learned that from Beyonce, and I feel like whatever Beyonce does, I do. So, yes, that's how I do it, basically.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: And so, when you hear everyone start to sing your words back to you, you know, the song that you've written and you're performing, over and over again, what's that like for you?

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: Oh, it's just -- it never gets old or boring. Every single time, it's a different feeling, you know. And being here, like, the atmosphere is so beautiful, and everyone's in such a good mood.And well, apart from the fight that happened.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: There was a -- there was a fight.

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: There was a fight for some reason. Everyone was just like feeling this height.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: Your music doesn't make me think I should fight.

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: No, I don't associate with my music with fighting. But like, since like I was saying to you earlier, like, I'm a boxer and I love to box. I love to sing. And I don't know, maybe there's some kind of weird parallel, but, like, everyone was really pumped.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: Yes, they were definitely pumped.Now, you came here from Las Vegas, and you performed in the Sphere. Just, like, in a couple of words, what was that experience like?

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: Absolutely mind-blowing. It was like, honestly, I couldn't compute it. I couldn't compute it in my head. It's -- I don't know if you've seen -- if anyone's seen what's going on in the Sphere, but Andrea (ph) was playing there, and I have a song with him. And it was myself. Grimes was there, FKA Twigs was there.And to see it like that and to be a part of that, my face -- my big old face on that screen, was like, hard to compute, but it was phenomenal. One of the coolest things that ever happened to me in my whole career.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: It was -- it looks really cool what you just showed me.So, this is a New Year for the world, but it's also a new year for you because, well, now, two days ago was your birthday.

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: I'm like, I'm just going to go with, like, I'm like de- aging. And like, I've been biohacking a lot lately. And like, I feel like I'm now like 35. I'm going to go with 35.

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: From now on, I'm 35. And that's that.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: And that's where you're going to stand?

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: I think as fit as you are, you can decide wherever the heck you want to be.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: So now, what is your -- what is your plan for the new year, for your personal new year? And for 2025?

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: Well, my new year consists of an album. I have my sixth album coming, and I'm going to be touring that. And I'm going to be doing a bit of acting and, like, doing a little bit of everything. ELAM

utterances.speaker: GOULDING
utterances.sentences: Yes, keeping up with the training. Might do a fight, might do a boxing fight. So, I don't know. Who knows? A lot, a lot.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: And love it like you do.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: Ellie Goulding, you were so fun to watch. Thank you. Happy New Year.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: I'm so glad to have you here.Sara, Cari and Harry, we have had a ball here on the Bahamas. I mean, you guys are having a ball there, too. I know. But I think -- I think we still win, because we're in the Bahamas.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Yes. No, Stephanie. Stephanie, you have the gig. We're not even going to compete. You have it. We are jealous. But we still love you.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: She called me by all three syllables.

utterances.speaker: ELAM
utterances.sentences: I love you, too. Happy New Year, guys.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year to you and Ellie there. Tell Ellie I said, "Hey up, me doc." Happy New Year to you both. This --

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: We can be in the Bahamas next year.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: It would be warmer. I was expecting warmer down here. I know, you know, in the center part of the country --/

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: -- despite the latitude, the longitude plays a little bit against you. But at least it wasn't raining here. We didn't -- you know.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You know, he looks as if he has a tan, though. Where are you coming from?

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: I do have -- you know, I did the George Hamilton treatment earlier today, but told them a little bit less.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: A little bit less. But the bottom line is, you know what? When you're on for New Year's Eve, you got to look good. So --

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You have to look your best.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: I'm competing against you, too. It's not really quite fair to me, but whatever.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Especially this glamazon over here. Like --

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I don't have a hat. I'm going to bring my hat in. I just wanted you all to have your moment. And when I bring my hat, I'm going to set it off.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: I will say this. The great thing about being in Austin -- and I know people talk about Austin as if it's the only place where you see South by Southwest -- but this city is so progressive. There's so much fun here.Last year, Sara and I had such a good opportunity to interview the mayor, talk about all the great things that they wanted to do with the city. They obviously have a huge, huge fan base with Texas, and obviously, they're in the Peach Bowl. Well get to that. Because you talked about the U.T. dancers. But the reason why I like being here, specifically, Harry, is because I can dance better than just about everyone here. And otherwise, I don't have great rhythm. But this is my time. ENTEN: No, I think this is your time. And I mean, the bottom line is this. They put me next to you to make you look even better.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: -- it's just. I don't even know what it is. You know, it almost looks like a dry heave in some sort of way.But I love Austin. This is my second time being to Austin. I once gave a political talk back in Austin. But more than that, I was able to get frozen yogurt twice from TCBY, and I couldn't do that back in New York. So, that's my new Austin thing.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: You are best friends in some capacity.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: She took my mom to see a movie, and I didn't even go.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: It's true. I'm in the family. I'm in the family.

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: We're all a band here.And speaking of bands, one of my favorites, we're going back to the childhood band for me. A performance from the legendary R&B group. You may know them as New Edition. I know them all as my boyfriends when I was a teenager. Here's a look at New Edition's residency at Wynn Las Vegas. (BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: I love that song. We are jamming out, dancing to "Mr. Telephone Man," which was from 1984. Dang. I'm old.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Oh, we know, and it hurts my -- my heart. Good night. You're out of here.Here's the funny part. On the stage, they've got the telephone booth from the streets back in the day when you had to put $0.10, $0.25 in there. And I bet you that half the people that are there --

utterances.speaker: CHAMPION
utterances.sentences: Have you ever used a telephone booth?

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: No, of course, I've used a telephone booth. Come on, there's a telephone --

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: Many a times. I used to call 1-800-COLLECT to my mom at baseball camp.

utterances.speaker: SIDNER
utterances.sentences: Oh, I thought you said for prison. You were calling her collect.

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: Look, we're not talking about my past life. It's about the future. We're turning --

utterances.speaker: ENTEN
utterances.sentences: -- over a new leaf on New Year's. Please, let's not make --
